E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Bozeman Reaction: After Leonard and Sheldon's flat is burgled, the gang create a new state-of-the-art security system to outwit any thieves and protect the place. (S3 Ep13)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Einstein Approximation: Sheldon is baffled by a formula he's working on, so he gets a less mentally taxing job at the Cheesecake Factory to kick-start his creativity. (S3 Ep14)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Large Hadron Collision: Sheldon is gutted when Leonard asks Penny to go to Switzerland on Valentine's Day to see the world's largest particle accelerator instead of him. (S3 Ep15)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Girl's in the Band: Lisa joins an advanced youth orchestra in Capital City, while Homer works the night shift and nearly goes mad. (S30 Ep19/23)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: I'm Just a Girl Who Can't Say D'oh: Marge directs a musical, but her leading man walks out and a thunderstorm threatens the live production... (S30 Ep20/23)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Justice League Recombination: The guys slowly warm to Zack and find an enjoyable way to bond with him when they enter a New Year's Eve fancy dress competition together. (S4 Ep11)

E4Plus1.uk.description: The Bus Pants Utilization: Leonard and Sheldon fight for control of an idea for an app. (S4 Ep12)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Love Car Displacement: Howard feels threatened when Bernadette runs into her hulk of an ex-boyfriend at a science conference. (S4 Ep13)

E4Plus1.uk.description: Franca Sozzani: The final five arrive in Marrakech, where one model's upset about having to share a bed with two of her competitors, and there's a shoot involving camels. (S16 Ep10)

E4Plus1.uk.description: Tattooed yoga lover Jak, vibrant 70-year-old fashion stylist Christine and Stetson-wearing Simon from Dallas are among the diners looking for love. (S9 Ep12)

E4Plus1.uk.description: The Closure Alternative: Amy employs a series of exercises to cure Sheldon of his compulsion to complete every task without fail and seek closure for every incident. (S6 Ep21)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Proton Resurgence: Leonard and Sheldon hire Professor Proton, the host of a TV science show they watched as children, to come to their flat and entertain them. (S6 Ep22)

E4Plus1.uk.description: We Need to Talk About Lily: Phil thinks he's found Pepper's dream home. Mitch and Cam get invited to an exclusive event. (S10 Ep14)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Goldbergs
E4Plus1.uk.description: Kara-Te: On the eve of the annual high school talent show, Beverly and Murray fall out over Barry's plan to perform his martial arts routine on stage. (S1 Ep11)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Goldbergs
E4Plus1.uk.description: You're Under Foot: When Beverly complains that Pops is spending too much time with her at home, Murray takes him back to work at the furniture shop. (S1 Ep12)

E4Plus1.uk.description: Welcome to the Pit Stop, How May I Help You?: Calvin soon regrets agreeing to Dave's suggestion for how to promote his business. (S5 Ep2)

E4Plus1.uk.description: Bart Gets an Elephant: Bart wins an elephant, but Homer can't afford its upkeep and decides to sell it to an ivory dealer... (S5 Ep17/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Hollyoaks
E4Plus1.uk.description: Ste tries to do the right thing, but a text leads Lucas to jump to conclusions. Elsewhere, a resident fights to keep the past hidden and Liberty tries to pull her family back together.

E4Plus1.uk.description: Daniella Issa Helayel: The remaining models are steeped in local culture in Marrakech, with a lesson in tea-tray dancing and some local grub including eyeballs and goat's brain. (S16 Ep11)

Film4.uk.title: Die Hard
Film4.uk.description: (1988) Action-thriller with Bruce Willis and Alan Rickman. Can a New York cop free the hostages being held in a skyscraper by an arch villain? Yippee ki-yay... whoops, can't say that here.

Film4.uk.title: Apocalypse Now
Film4.uk.description: (1979) Final cut of Coppola's award-laden take on the Vietnam War, with Martin Sheen and Marlon Brando. An assassin travels upriver to terminate a renegade colonel with extreme prejudice.

Film4.uk.title: Teleshopping
Film4.uk.description: Teleshopping.

Film4.uk.title: Teleshopping
Film4.uk.description: Teleshopping.

Film4.uk.title: Patrick
Film4.uk.description: (2018) Feel-good British family comedy. Sarah's (Beattie Edmondson) chaotic life gets even more complicated when she inherits a naughty pug from her nan.

Film4.uk.title: The Call of the Wild
Film4.uk.description: (2020) Touching adventure with Harrison Ford, based on Jack London's classic novel. A big, friendly hound finds himself unwittingly travelling across late 19th-century North America.

Film4.uk.title: Dad's Army
Film4.uk.description: (1971) Film version of the popular comedy series set in 1940. The Walmington-on-Sea Home Guard, led by Arthur Lowe's Captain Mainwaring, bumble through a series of misadventures.

Film4.uk.title: Home Alone
Film4.uk.description: (1990) Classic family comedy starring Macaulay Culkin. A boy's parents forget to take him on holiday with them. Then two inept burglars turn up. Can our resourceful young hero outwit them?

Film4.uk.title: Home Alone 2: Lost in New York
Film4.uk.description: (1992) Family comedy. Macaulay Culkin ends up in a swish New York hotel while his family are in Miami. But the burglars he defeated before (Joe Pesci and Daniel Stern) are back...

Film4.uk.title: The Northman
Film4.uk.description: (2022) Epic Viking saga starring Alexander Skarsgrd as a warrior prince who goes on the rampage to Iceland to avenge his murdered father. With Ethan Hawke, Nicole Kidman and Bjrk.

Film4.uk.title: Free Guy
Film4.uk.description: (2021) Comedy action starring Ryan Reynolds. Guy lives in Free City. Free City isn't real. Nor is Guy. It's all a big online game. Can he take down the corrupt game publisher?

Film4.uk.title: Werewolves Within
Film4.uk.description: (2021) Comedy horror with Milana Vayntrub. A park ranger is sent to a town where everyone is at each other's throats, figuratively at first, but then literally. Is a werewolf to blame?

Film4.uk.description: Fifth episode of the award-winning sketch show in BSL, with a range of deaf characters. Subtitled for the deaf-impaired. [SL]

Film4.uk.title: Teleshopping
Film4.uk.description: Teleshopping.

Film4.uk.title: Carrington, VC
Film4.uk.description: (1954) Anthony Asquith's vivid and subtle courtroom drama casts David Niven as the eponymous officer accused of stealing army money and going absent without leave.

Film4.uk.title: Pool of London
Film4.uk.description: (1951) Classic Ealing thriller filmed in a documentary style, starring Bonar Colleano as a sailor whose smuggling activities lead to him being suspected of murder and going on the run.

Film4.uk.title: The Fallen Idol
Film4.uk.description: (1948) Adaptation of Graham Greene's story with Ralph Richardson and Bobby Henrey. A butler who is accused of murdering his wife, has only a schoolboy to fight his corner.

Film4.uk.title: Fatherhood
Film4.uk.description: (2021) Heartfelt fact-based comedy-drama. Kevin Hart stars as a widower who is suddenly sprung into single fatherhood after his wife dies a day after giving birth.

Film4.uk.title: Central Intelligence
Film4.uk.description: (2016) Action-comedy with Dwayne Johnson and Kevin Hart. Two former school buddies team up to thwart a terrorist plot. But things may not be as they seem. With Amy Ryan and Jason Bateman.

Film4.uk.title: Violent Night
Film4.uk.description: (2022) A gang of violent home-invaders find out the hard way that you REALLY don't want to be on Santa's naughty list, in Tommy Wirkola's dark, violent Christmas comedy. With David Harbour.

Film4.uk.title: S.W.A.T.
Film4.uk.description: (2003) Action with Colin Farrell and Samuel L Jackson. A loose canon joins an elite force to escort a fugitive to chokey. But the baddie's put a reward out for help with his escape.

Film4.uk.title: Mothering Sunday
Film4.uk.description: (2021) Romantic drama with Odessa Young and Olivia Colman. In 20s England, a writer working as a maid has a passionate affair with the rich boy next door. It's not considered a good match.

Film4.uk.description: Teleshopping.

Film4.uk.description: Teleshopping.

Film4.uk.title: Arizona Raiders
Film4.uk.description: (1965) William Whitney's brutal western. Two former Confederate rebels are offered their freedom if they can track, catch or even kill their former gang mates. Starring Audie Murphy.

Film4.uk.title: Cover Girl
Film4.uk.description: (1944) Rita Hayworth and Gene Kelly star in Charles Vidor's Technicolor comedy musical about a chorus girl's rise to fame. Featuring songs and a score from Jerome Kern and Ira Gershwin.

Film4.uk.title: Gift Horse
Film4.uk.description: (1952) War drama. Trevor Howard plays the captain of an ageing US warship, gifted to the British navy, which is chosen to lead the raid on Saint-Nazaire in 1942. With Richard Attenborough.

Film4.uk.title: The Moonraker
Film4.uk.description: (1958) Romantic thriller. George Baker stars as a heroic Cavalier horseman, beating off the Roundhead foe as he single-handedly smuggles the country's aristocracy to safety in France.

Film4.uk.title: Instant Family
Film4.uk.description: (2018) Comedy. Mark Wahlberg and Rose Byrne star as a couple whose orderly lives are disrupted when they foster three kids. Based on director Sean Anders' own experience.

Film4.uk.title: Transporter 2
Film4.uk.description: (2005) Violent action-thriller starring Jason Statham as the tough courier Frank Martin, who's hired to guard a government drugs czar's son. But his mission soon lurches towards disaster.

Film4.uk.title: Inglourious Basterds
Film4.uk.description: (2009) Quentin Tarantino's World War II action-adventure. Jewish American soldiers go Nazi-hunting in occupied France. With Brad Pitt, Diane Kruger, Christoph Waltz and Michael Fassbender.
